short_description: Stable Value Fund Investment Management Services
description:
By this notice we announce the publication of a Request for Proposals (RFP) document from the Board of Trustees of the Maryland Teachers and State Employees Supplemental Retirement Plans (the "Board"). This RFP seeks proposals from qualified parties for a successor stable value manager.  The RFP package is attached to this email and is also available on the Internet from the Board?s website (MSRP.maryland.gov) and from the website for Maryland state government commerce (https://eMaryland.buyspeed.com/bso/). 

The Board by statute is the governing body for most supplemental retirement plans available to employees of the State of Maryland.  The Board maintains four plans: a grandfathered 401(k) plan; a 457(b) plan; a 403(b) plan; and 401(a) match plan.  Total assets for all plans are approximately $3 billion.

The Board currently maintains a benefit responsive stable value fund, known as the MSRP
nigp_class_with_description: 946 - FINANCIAL SERVICES

description:
By this notice we announce the publication of a Request for Proposals (RFP) document from the Board of Trustees of the Maryland Teachers and State Employees Supplemental Retirement Plans (the "Board"). This RFP seeks proposals from qualified parties for a successor stable value manager.  The RFP package is attached to this email and is also available on the Internet from the Board?s website (MSRP.maryland.gov) and from the website for Maryland state government commerce (https://eMaryland.buyspeed.com/bso/). 

The Board by statute is the governing body for most supplemental retirement plans available to employees of the State of Maryland.  The Board maintains four plans: a grandfathered 401(k) plan; a 457(b) plan; a 403(b) plan; and 401(a) match plan.  Total assets for all plans are approximately $3 billion.

The Board currently maintains a benefit responsive stable value fund, known as the MSRP

The campaign will raise awareness of the affordability, accessibility and benefits of a post secondary education in Maryland.

description: This RFP is to provide software support, Maintenance and Enhancement services for its Maryland College Aid Processing System (MDCAPS), the state financial aid management system. MDCAPS, is a web-based comprehensive and customized database system that provides the services necessary for MHEC?s Office of Student Financial Assistance (OSFA) and our customers to manage financial aid programs and services.  In addition, a non-web-based module of MDCAPS is the Service Obligation and Loan Repayment (SOLR) system, which is a desktop application designed for the management of programs which have associated service and/or repayment requirements.

description: The State Board of Elections (SBE) is offering a full time position for an individual with experience in Visual Basic 6, Oracle, SQL, Crystal Reports, HTML, and election management processes. description:
SBE requires a part time Technical and Administrative Assistant with experience in the Maryland election processes, including campaign finance.
